<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
Amongst Brazilian species of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Ipomoea" order="Solanales" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Ipomoea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="I." lsidName="I. scopulina" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" rank="species" species="scopulina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">I. scopulina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles only 
<taxonomicName genus="I." lsidName="I. longistaminea" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" rank="species" species="longistaminea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">I. longistaminea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="O’Donell">O'Donell</normalizedToken>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="I." lsidName="I. ana-mariae" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" rank="species" species="ana-mariae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">I. ana-mariae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L.V.Vasconcelos &amp; Sim.-Bianch in having a cylindrical suburceolate corolla but is distinguished from both of these by the broadly lanceolate subacute (not oblong-elliptic, coriaceous, somewhat concave) sepals.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
